        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(openai): add GPT-5.6 series support",
        "body": "Closes #98296\n\nRelated: #98021 (`ultra` orchestration remains separate)\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw does not recognize the limited-preview GPT-5.6 Sol, Terra, and Luna model IDs across its direct OpenAI, ChatGPT/Codex OAuth, simple-completion, and Codex App Server paths. Users with preview access cannot select the models reliably or use their `max` reasoning effort, and stale fallback metadata can route them with the wrong transport or effort.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdd the three public GPT-5.6 model contracts with current preview pricing, 372k context metadata, text/image input, and model-aware `minimal`/`max` reasoning normalization while keeping `openai/gpt-5.5` as the default. Upgrade the Codex App Server package to 0.142.4, refresh its generated protocol schemas and documented model snapshot, and treat live App Server reasoning metadata as authoritative without mistaking synthetic fallback rows for live capability data.\n\n## User Impact\n\nOrganizations with GPT-5.6 preview access can use `openai/gpt-5.6-sol`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra`, and `openai/gpt-5.6-luna` through API-key, ChatGPT/Codex OAuth, simple-completion, and Codex App Server workflows. `max` is preserved for the series, unsupported `minimal` requests normalize to `low`, older/Azure routes retain their prior clamps, and GPT-5.5 remains the default.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Official contract checked against [OpenAI's GPT-5.6 preview announcement](https://openai.com/index/previewing-gpt-5-6-sol-terra-and-luna/), [preview access/pricing details](https://help.openai.com/en/articles/20001325-a-preview-of-gpt-5-6-sol-terra-and-luna), and [model-selection guidance](https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/models).\n- Live E2E: `openclaw agent --local --model openai/gpt-5.6-luna --thinking max` returned the exact expected reply with provider `openai`, model `gpt-5.6-luna`, harness `codex`, 372000 context tokens, `thinking=max`, no fallback, and a successful stop.\n- Exact `@openai/codex` 0.142.4 `model/list` discovery confirmed the public Sol/Terra/Luna rows and supported efforts; protocol schemas were regenerated from the matching `rust-v0.142.4` tag.\n- Blacksmith Testbox `tbx_01kwdmwncj2atwwfatz3144jkx`: 303 focused changed-surface tests passed across OpenAI, agent, Codex, and App Server shards; `pnpm tsgo:all` passed.\n- `pnpm build`, focused `oxlint`, and `git diff --check` passed.\n- Fresh local autoreview completed with no accepted/actionable findings.\n",
